# MATLAB MCP Server - Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and customize for your system

# =============================================================================
# MATLAB Library Path Configuration
# =============================================================================
# Only needed if MATLAB is NOT installed in the default location
# or if you encounter "library not found" errors

# macOS (Apple Silicon - M1/M2/M3)
# DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=/Applications/MATLAB_R2025b.app/bin/maca64

# macOS (Intel)
# DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=/Applications/MATLAB_R2025b.app/bin/maci64

# Linux (64-bit)
# LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/MATLAB/R2025b/bin/glnxa64

# Windows (usually not needed - installer handles this)
# PATH=C:\Program Files\MATLAB\R2025b\bin\win64

# =============================================================================
# Default MATLAB Locations
# =============================================================================
# macOS:  /Applications/MATLAB_R2025b.app
# Linux:  /usr/local/MATLAB/R2025b
# Windows: C:\Program Files\MATLAB\R2025b

# =============================================================================
# Auto-Setup Instructions
# =============================================================================
# Run the helper script to auto-detect your MATLAB installation:
#   uv run scripts/setup_matlab_env.py
#
# This will create a .env file with the correct paths for your system.

# =============================================================================
# Version Matching
# =============================================================================
# Make sure your matlabengine version matches your MATLAB installation:
#   R2026a -> matlabengine 26.1.x
#   R2025b -> matlabengine 25.2.x
#   R2025a -> matlabengine 25.1.x
#   R2024b -> matlabengine 24.2.x
#   R2024a -> matlabengine 24.1.x
#
# Install specific version:
#   uv pip install matlabengine==25.2.0

# =============================================================================
# Usage
# =============================================================================
# After creating .env with your paths, run commands with:
#   uv run --env-file .env matlab-cli -c "disp('Hello MATLAB')"
#   uv run --env-file .env matlab-mcp
